The paper deals with image classification using sparse coding, which is a popular technique in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel approach to sparse coding by adding non-convex and non-negative characters, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Scale Invariant Feature Transform (SIFT) descriptors is also a common technique in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several databases, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
